3:
So the land is drying up,\q and everyone living in it is wasting away;
\q the beasts in the fields and the birds in the sky,
\q even the fish in the sea, are being taken away.

9:
It will be the same for the people as for the priests:\q I will punish them all for their practices;
\q I will repay them for their deeds.


\q

18:
Even when their strong drink is gone,\q they continue to commit adultery;
\q her rulers dearly love their shame.
\q
